1.source code 

./configure
make
make install

advantage: compatible
disadvantage: time; dependibility

2.RPM
different op with different RPM

"software name" - "version" . "OP" . "64/32"
linuxcast-1.2.0-30.el6.i686.rpm

rpm -i software.rpm
rpm -e software ;erase
rpm -U software-new.rpm

rpm  -ivh http://www.linuxcast.net/software.rpm
-v visual
-h processing bar

Search
rpm -qa ;a all
rpm -qi LinuxCast.net ;i install
rpm -ql ;l list
rpm -qf /usr/bin/linuxcast ;to see which softwar intrduced /usr/bin/linuxcast

not installed
rpm -qip
rpm -qlp

3.YUM(Yellowdog Updater, Modified)
Yum, to solve the dependency problem in RPMh

repo (repository)
/etc/yum.repos.d

yum install software-name
yum remove software-name
yum update software-name

Search
yum search vnc
yum list (installed|recent|updates|installed)

ll | wc -l
